14/09/2003
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Prime Minister Branko Crvenkovski and Democratic Union of Integration leader Ali Ahmeti have reportedly overcome misunderstandings that followed recent military action in Brest.
According to party officials, the two leaders met Saturday (13 September) and settled issues related to security operations by government forces.
They agreed on the need to deal with armed criminal groups.
Security forces are working to arrest a pair of ethnic Albanian extremist leaders, Avdil Jakupi and Hamdi Bajrami.
(MIA, Makfax - 13/09/03)
